			}]
			title: "Fishing"
			x: 1.5d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["PR01000000000001"]
			description: ["Tools in Mine and Slash gain levels through use. As a tool levels up, it accumulates affixes — passive bonuses that improve its performance. A tool gains one new affix every 20 levels. High-level tools with strong affix rolls significantly outperform fresh tools: a level 80 pickaxe with mining speed and Tiered Ore affixes mines faster and yields more profession materials than an identical iron pickaxe. Tools cannot be repaired — replace them when spent."]
			id: "PR01000000000005"
			rewards: [{
				count: 4
				id: "PR03000000000005"
				item: "minecraft:iron_ingot"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "PR02000000000005"
				title: "Level a Mine and Slash tool to at least level 20"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Leveling Tools"
			x: 4.5d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["PR01000000000001"]
			description: ["The Salvaging Station deconstructs gear into Stones — Rarity-graded materials used in Gear Crafting, Infusing, and quality improvement. Higher rarity gear yields higher rarity Stones. Place gear into a hopper above the Salvaging Station for manual salvage at higher yields. Auto-salvaging through the MnS Hub is available but returns less Stone. Salvaging is the primary source of Common, Uncommon, and Rare Stones — all critical inputs for every crafting profession in the game."]
			id: "PR01000000000006"
			rewards: [{
				count: 16
				id: "PR03000000000006"
				item: "mmorpg:stone/1"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "PR02000000000006"
				item: "mmorpg:salvaging_station"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Salvaging"
			x: -4.5d
			y: -4.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["PR01000000000006", "PR01000000000002"]
			description: ["The Gear Crafting Station produces Crafted Gear Souls: armor, offhand, jewelry, and weapon souls that can be equipped and carry full affix rolls. Gear Crafting requires three components: Tiered Ore (determines the item level of the output), Stones (determine rarity), and Ingots with an Identifier Item (determines the gear slot). The result is a craftable gear soul of chosen slot, level, and rarity — bypassing the randomness of drops. Check JEI for exact recipe requirements."]
			id: "PR01000000000007"
			rewards: [{
				count: 5
				id: "PR03000000000007"
				item: "mmorpg:stone/1"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "PR02000000000007"
				item: "mmorpg:gear_crafting_station"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Gear Crafting"
			x: -1.5d
			y: -4.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["PR01000000000003"]
			description: ["The Cooking Station produces MnS food items that grant temporary stat bonuses when consumed. Cooking recipes use Tiered Meat, Tiered Produce, or Tiered Fish as the primary ingredient — the type determines the effect category. Meat-based foods provide Health and Magic Shield Regen; Produce-based foods provide Mana and Energy Regen; Fish-based foods provide Experience and Loot bonuses. Each recipe also requires one Stone (for rarity) and a secondary food ingredient. Check JEI for specific recipes."]
			id: "PR01000000000008"
			rewards: [{
				count: 5
				id: "PR03000000000008"
				item: "mmorpg:material/meat/0"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "PR02000000000008"
				item: "mmorpg:cooking_station"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Cooking"
			x: 0.0d
			y: -4.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["PR01000000000001"]
			description: ["The Alchemy Station brews potions that provide temporary combat stat boosts. Alchemy recipes use Tiered ingredients as the base: Meat yields Health and Resource Potions; Produce yields Core Stat Potions; Fish yields Damage Buff Potions. Additionally, one Stone (for rarity) and 1-2 secondary food items are required per recipe. Unlike vanilla potions, MnS potions scale with the tier of ingredients used — higher tiers produce stronger and longer-duration effects. Check JEI for specific recipes."]
			id: "PR01000000000009"
			rewards: [{
				count: 5
				id: "PR03000000000009"
				item: "mmorpg:material/farming/0"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "PR02000000000009"
				item: "mmorpg:alchemy_station"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "MnS Alchemy"
			x: 1.5d
			y: -4.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["PR01000000000007"]
			description: ["The Enchanting Station (Infusing Profession) crafts Infusion Scrolls — consumables applied to gear that add a bonus stat. An Infusion Scroll recipe requires Tiered Ore, Stones (rarity), Ingots, Identifier Items, Paper, and coin. When applied to gear, the Infusion has a chance of success and grants a stat bonus determined by rarity. Infusions must be applied in rarity order — you cannot apply a Rare scroll to an item that has no Uncommon infusion yet. Failed infusions are consumed."]
			id: "PR01000000000010"
			rewards: [{
				count: 4
				id: "PR03000000000010"
				item: "minecraft:paper"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "PR02000000000010"
				item: "mmorpg:enchanting_station"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Infusing"
			x: 4.5d
			y: -4.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["PR01000000000007"]
			description: ["Sharpening Stones increase the base quality of a piece of gear — improving the gear's primary stat (Weapon Damage, Armor, Dodge Rating, etc.) beyond its natural roll cap. Craft Sharpening Stones at the Gear Crafting Station using Stones of the appropriate rarity. A higher rarity Sharpening Stone applies a larger quality bonus. Sharpening Stones can only be applied once per item and stack on top of Orbs of Quality — always apply Orbs first, then Sharpen."]
			id: "PR01000000000011"
